HEADWORD: Pauperism
<hw>Pau"per*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>paup⟦eacute⟧risme</ets>.]</ety> <def>The state of being a pauper;
the state of indigent persons requiring support from the
community.</def> <rj><au>Whatly.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Poverty; indigence; penury; want; need;
destitution. See <er>Poverty</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pauperization</ent>⟦br⟧
